messages.message:
Reiterating this point :point_up:

Please can we urgently get a stable instance of AI Hub set up for GTM to use. Something got pushed in the last 10 minutes to UAT that has broken build mode AND converse mode

How can we get this issue resolved asap for any SEs that have demos planned today?

CC @Anant @Kerry @Clemens @Varun Jain
this is licensing / usage error. @Matt Weaver can you check if you still have enough credit on UAT
cc @mfichman -- can you help with this? did someone change something on UAT?
side note that we should present a more user friendly message here when there's a genuine licensing error :slightly_smiling_face:
If there's a super urgent deadline, we can mitigate by temporarily disabling licensing. Will wait on Matt for guidance until then.
Yes please @Pridhvi Vegesna. The SE Team are actively using this env for demos
Ok Shaunak I'm pushing 4 patches to disable licensing in api-server, webapp, apps-server, and app-tasks
Is the env working for you now @Matt Weaver

@shaunak Asked me to re-enable it on UAT.

The fix for that error is to empty your browser cache!
EDIT: The backend fix for this did _not_ make it the codecut yesterday, so I'm cherry-picking it (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/41087). We should keep licensing disabled.
Yes, I had asked @mfichman to enable licensing.  Let’s disable it for now.  And we’ll do another code cut in the evening.
